Description: Ostracon, fragment from the body of a brown pottery meat-jar, fabric has small white inclusions, exterior covered with a cream-coloured slip, with remains of three lines of black-painted hieratic text on the exterior specifying the contents as pressed meat of year 7.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (389873) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/389873)
